data.body:
Rather than duplicating:

```
if (err != null) {
  new SupClient.dialogs.InfoDialog(err, SupClient.i18n.t("common:actions.close"));
  return;
}
```

in our edit asset callbacks everywhere, `SupClient.projectClient.editAsset` and `.editResource` should do it by default (and we can always provide an alternative version that doesn't, if needed).

See also: https://github.com/superpowers/superpowers-game/issues/41
